    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There's no difference in JS between:\n\n``` js\nvar obj = {\n  ['facet']: ['lang'] // computed property name resolving to 'facet'\n}\n```\n\n[Computed properties](https://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Object_initializer#Computed_property_names)\n\nand\n\n``` js\nvar obj = {\n  'facet': ['lang']\n}\n```\n\nor\n\n``` js\nvar obj = {\n  facet: ['lang'] // no need for '' since no special character\n}\n```\n\nThey all resolve to the same object structure.\n\nThe original issue and description is not what we are looking for, open a new issue if you remember the exact problem.\n",
